Brazilian President Starts Asia Tour
The visit to East Timor symbolizes Brazil's commitment to participate
in the reconstruction process in the Asian country, said the Brazilian
Foreign Ministry.
During his eight-hour stay in Dili, capital of East Timor, Cardoso will
meet with Xanana Gusmao, president of the National Timorese Resistance
Council, and with Nobel Peace Prize laureates Bishop Carlos Ximenes
Belo and Jose Ramos Horta.
Cardoso will visit in Indonesia on January 23, where he will hold talks
with President Abdurrahman Wahid and meet with Vice- President Megawati
Sukarnoputri.
The Brazilian Foreign Ministry said that Cardoso's visit to Indonesia
represents the political will of Brazil to carry out mature bilateral
relations with Indonesia as the two countries have great potential for
economic and commercial cooperation.
